<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="8" bgcolor="#E9D7B9"><tr><td>
<font class="title">Hierarchy</font><br><font class="content">FlameKeepers of Norrath<br><br><br><br><p align="justify">First and foremost, the Council of Elders believes in open channels of communication. For that reason, there is no "chain of command". Any member may approach an Advisor or Elder with problems, ideas, requests, or just to say "hello". If ye feel ye have not been heard, do not hesitate to contact another Elder or Advisor. We cannot stress enough how important communication is - if we don't know, we can't help.<br />
<br />
</p><br><p align="justify">Our family is a team and we will strive to work together in all avenues. As members move through the posts, the Council of Elders expects increased interaction within all areas described - from guild functions (planning, hosting, volunteering) to recruitment and everything in between. <br><br>

FlameKeepers of Norrath is based upon an unusual system where posts are attained by self-appointed quest/deeds. There are only 6 posts, outside of the Council of Elders. Below is the tree. <br><br>

<b>Council of Elders</b> <br><br>

a. <b>HighKeeper-Guild Leader</b> - Maintain site, communication avenues (boards, emails, news)<br><br>

b. <b>Sage</b> - Helps members with information relative to game/guild.<br><br>

c. <b>ArchPriest/ess</b> - Ambassador and Master/Mistress of Ceremonies<br><br>

d. <b>QuestMaster</b> - Oversees all members and seekers on quest, in charge of Torchlighter's Brigade ("JV" Raid Team).<br><br>

Members can attain Elder status but be forewarned - the road is long and arduous though worth the trip. Active CoE members reserve the right to decide when an Advisor will be invited to join the Elders Council. An Advisor will only be invited if the Council of Elders has unanimously agreed to do so.<br><br>

<b>Advisor & Advisor with Quest Title (Officer Status) </b><br><br>

Advisor(Officer Status) is attained in slightly different manner than other posts. Only those members who have performed at least one quest to move to a new post will be considered for officer positions, as needed.   It is preferable to continue questing to reach Protector/Titled, however, as need requires, the CoE may invite a member who has not attained this rank.  <br><br>

Officers are members who have dedicated much time and energy (and must be willing to continue to do so!) into the guild and have shown excellent leadership traits throughout their time. Officers must be able and willing to assist members in all areas needed with efficiency, objectivity, and good spirits. <br><br>

<blockquote><b>Protector & Protector with Quest Title</b> - Advisors' aides(assist as needed), "Advisors In Training" Honor Guard of FKoN (meeting guards). </blockquote>

<blockquote><b>Knight & Knight with Quest Title</b> - QuestMaster Assistants - aid in over-seeing questing members and apprentices, actively participate in Torchlighter's Brigade.</blockquote>

<blockquote><b>Cavalier & Cavalier with Quest Title</b> - Assist Initiates as needed, familiarize them with guild on continual basis, assist Apprentices in quests.</blockquote>

<blockquote><b>Initiate</b> - "Mentor" Seekers, assist them with questions they may have, learn and expand on basic raiding techniques.</blockquote>

<blockquote><b>Apprentice (90 Day Probationary Tag)</b> - Apprentices should use the 90 days to get a feel for the guild - complete their assigned quests, meet folks, post on boards, visit website for news and events.</blockquote>

<blockquote><b>Seekers</b> - A Seeker's main responsibility is to get to know the members and obtain 3 letters of support from Keepers so they may be tagged as Apprentice.</blockquote>

<b>Questing</b><br><br>

In order to "step-up" a post within FKoN, all members must do the following:<br><br>

1. Submit a written, in-character request to all members of the Council stating the post you are questing for. Remember - you may only move one step at a time. You may, however, submit two part quests to attain new posts. <br><br>

2. If you are questing for your titled post, you MUST choose a special "title" which only you will hold within that post. Example: Cavalier and then name your special title for that post. Example: Cavalier Protector. CAVALIER PROTECTOR AND CAVALIER WILL BE THE SAME RANK - one is not 'higher' than the other. <br><br>

3. You MUST decide upon a quest or swear an oath to perform some deed that you feel adequately represents the post/title which you have chosen to attain. The Elders will decide whether that oath of deed/quest is adequate (based on the post you are applying for) and then will inform you of their approval within 3-5 days of your submission. We will also offer suggestions if we do not feel that your proposal is adequate. You may accept, reject, or counteroffer these suggestions without fear of consequence until such a time when both parties (Member and Council) are agreed. <br><br>

4. You will then perform what you have sworn to do, in order to obtain the post and title that you have chosen, with due proof of your work. Most likely, this will be the QuestMaster or QM Aides, who may "visit" you while you are doing so (and, in addition, you may choose to have witnesses provide testimonials.).<br><br>

5. The CoE will then convene and decide, unanimously, whether you have earned the "step-up" according to the actual performance of the oath of deed/quest that you have sworn to perform.<br><br>

You may only step up one post at a time, but you may do so in a way that you see fit, as long as it is approved and proven. The Council of Elders also holds the right to deny your attainment of a post (if you have not performed what you have sworn to do.).<br><br>

<b>Awards</b><br><br>

We, the Council of Elders, will also bestow special awards upon Keepers who have earned them, awards that are not given within the hierarchy, but are based upon the following:<br><br>

<table border=5 cellspacing=10 cellpadding=10 width="75%">
<tr><th>Symbol</th><th>Award Name</th><th>Reason</th></tr>
